          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-17-1693842511344-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the pot with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook over a low heat for 5-7 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency and once thickened, blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong></p><p>Season with a small pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, cover with a lid and set aside for later – this is your <strong>katsu curry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-16-1693842514297-x200.jpg",
